+# Phase 1 Skeleton Marker
+# ========================
+# Directory: src/capabilities/
+# Purpose:   Layer 2 — ClawCodex-specific Protocol definitions.
+
+# Role:      Define the interface contracts (Protocol classes) that
+#            Layer 3 (features) uses to communicate with Layer 1 (upstream).
+
+# Protocol philosophy:
+#   - Python's typing.Protocol (structural subtyping, no inheritance needed)
+#   - Informal interfaces — implementors declare `Protocol` and type-checker validates
+#   - NOT ABC (no forced inheritance), NOT dataclass (not data containers)
+
+# Phase 1 role: Create stub Protocol files with NotImplementedError stubs.
+# Phase 2/3:   Implement actual Protocol methods matching concrete classes.
+
+# Import rule (enforced by upstream-sync audit):
+#   src.capabilities may NOT import from src.upstream.
+#   src.capabilities may be imported by src.features (orchestrator, providers, etc.).
+
+# See: docs/UPSTREAM_SYNC_DESIGN-decoupling.md Section 4.2
+# See: upstream-sync.yaml layers[1] ("capabilities")
